data.enText: the process or result of sth becoming or being made larger
the enlargement of the company's overseas business activities

data.chText: 欧盟扩大得到了广泛的支持。
data.enText: There was widespread support for EU enlargement (= the fact of more countries joining).

data.chText: 扩大物，放大物（尤指照片）
data.enText: something that has been made larger, especially a photograph

data.chText: 如果你喜欢这照片，我可以给你寄一张放大的。
data.enText: If you like the picture I can send you an enlargement of it.

means: 扩大物，放大物(尤指照片)

tr: the act of increasing (something) in size or volume or quantity or scope
a photographic print that has been enlarged
a discussion that provides additional information

value.def: The enlargement of something is the process or result of making it bigger.

example.ex: There is insufficient space for enlargement of the buildings.
example.tran: 没有足够的空间扩建这些建筑。

gramarinfo.label: usu with supp, oft N <l>of</l> n

value.def: An enlargement is a photograph that has been made bigger.
value.tran: 扩印的照片;放大的照片
